# Model Tiering

A local proxy (`claude-code-router` on `127.0.0.1:3456`) routes each Claude Code call by requested model name, request shape, and estimated context size. Active local profile: **`{{ .localProfile }}`** (set at chezmoi init via the `localProfile` flag — `lean` | `fast` | `balanced` | `smart`; chezmoi init recommends a profile based on detected RAM, defaults to `lean` below 48 GB, `smart` at 48+ GB). Each profile has a hardware-aware ctx-size embedded in `/var/lib/llama.cpp/presets.ini` (chezmoi-rendered from `localNumCtx`, currently {{ .localNumCtx }}). Bump models by editing `~/.config/chezmoi/chezmoi.toml` then `chezmoi apply`.

Profile picks (q4_K_M weights, total RAM expected with usable ctx):

| Profile | code / prose / think | Style | RAM tier | App-cleanup expectation |
|---------|----------------------|-------|----------|-------------------------|
| `lean` | `qwen3-14b` / `gemma3-12b` / `qwen3-8b` | small dense, always fits | 16+ GB | none — runs alongside browsers |
| `fast` | `gemma4-26b-a4b` MoE / `gemma4-e4b` / `qwen3.6-35b-a3b` MoE | MoE-first, fastest decode, tiny prose | 32 GB w/ Chrome closed, 48+ GB comfortable | close heavy apps on 32 GB |
| `balanced` | `qwen3.6-35b-a3b` MoE / `gemma4-26b-a4b` MoE / `qwen3.6-35b-a3b` MoE | MoE everywhere, consistent quality | 32 GB w/ Chrome closed, 48+ GB comfortable | close heavy apps on 32 GB |
| `smart` | `qwen3.6-27b` dense / `gemma4-31b` dense / `qwen3.6-27b` dense | densest weights, highest single-shot quality, smallest ctx | 32 GB w/ Chrome closed (≤ 5K ctx prose lane), 48+ GB for full ctx | close all heavy apps on 32 GB |

Counter-intuitive: `smart` is the **heaviest** profile, not the leanest. Dense q4 31B (~20 GiB) beats MoE 35B-a3b (~17.5 GiB) on RAM despite the smaller nominal param count, because MoE compresses active params. Pick `smart` for quality per token; pick `fast`/`balanced` for MoE decode speed; pick `lean` when nothing else fits.

| Tier | Backend | Models | Triggers |
|------|---------|--------|----------|
| Local | llama.cpp (Vulkan, AMD 890M) router on :11434 | `{{ .local.code }}` (code), `{{ .local.prose }}` (prose), `{{ .local.think }}` (think) — qwen3 lanes use spec decode via `{{ .local.draft }}` | `model: haiku`. Trivial sonnet/opus. Borderline (with `defaultLocal`). Thinking field (only when `cloudThinking=false` and ctx ≤ 60K). Skill local-mode toggle. |
| Cloud Sonnet | Anthropic API | `{{ .cloud.sonnet }}` | Main session default. `model: sonnet`. Long context (>60K). Reasoning verbs. `webSearch`. |
| Cloud Opus | Anthropic API | `{{ .cloud.opus }}` | `model: opus` for non-trivial requests. Any thinking-field request when `cloudThinking=true` (default). |

Local requests route to one of three lanes based on content signals (lanes can collapse to the same model under `balanced`/`smart` profiles):

| Local model | Lane | Signals |
|-------------|------|---------|
| `{{ .local.code }}` | code | `.go` `.py` `.ts` etc. file refs; tool-heavy work; default lane; any request with `tools` (prose lane lacks tool support) |
| `{{ .local.prose }}` | prose | `.md` `.txt` refs, commit messages, Slack, design docs — only when request has no `tools` field |
| `{{ .local.think }}` | think | thinking-field requests when `cloudThinking=false` and ctx ≤ 60K |

**Thinking routing** is gated by the `cloudThinking` chezmoi flag (default `true`). When `true`, every thinking-field request goes to cloud Opus. When `false`, small-ctx thinking goes to the local think lane and only long-ctx thinking escapes to Opus.

Inline override keywords (anywhere in the last user message):

| Keyword | Routes to | Use when |
|---------|-----------|----------|
| `@code` | local `{{ .local.code }}` | force local code lane |
| `@prose` | local `{{ .local.prose }}` | force local prose lane |
| `@think` | local `{{ .local.think }}` | force local think lane |
| `@cloudcode` | cloud `{{ .cloud.sonnet }}` | force cloud Sonnet for code/general work |
| `@cloudprose` | cloud `{{ .cloud.sonnet }}` | force cloud Sonnet for prose |
| `@cloudthink` | cloud `{{ .cloud.opus }}` | force cloud Opus reasoning (big plans, hard analysis) |

**Subagent routing is automatic — leave the model name unset.** Plan sets `thinking`, so the router picks cloud Opus (default) or local think (`cloudThinking=false` + ctx ≤ 60K) regardless of model. Explore, cavecrew-*, and prose-review inherit `haiku` and route local.

**In Opus thinking sessions, delegate to subagents.** Direct `Read` / `Bash` / `Grep` / `Edit` calls stay on the main Opus chain and burn Opus tokens. Subagents spawn fresh haiku chains that land on local `{{ .local.code }}`. Reach for `Agent(Explore)` for file reads and greps, `Agent(cavecrew-investigator)` for code-locator tables, `Agent(cavecrew-builder)` for 1-2 file edits, `Agent(cavecrew-reviewer)` for diff reviews.

**Skill local-mode toggle** (for Notion-heavy maintenance work via `/health`, `/guitar-tutor` etc.):

```
/model local,{{ .local.prose }}      # switch main session to local (prose lane)
/model local,{{ .local.code }}       # switch main session to local (code lane)
/model local,{{ .local.think }}      # switch main session to local (think lane)
/model anthropic,{{ .cloud.sonnet }} # switch back to cloud
```

Use cloud Sonnet for cross-log analysis, training-plan design, schema restructures, and prose generation. Use local for mechanical row-level Notion edits and bulk operations.

**Audit routing decisions** with `claude-code-router-audit` (last 24h by default; supports `1h` / `7d` / `--since "..."` windows). Reads from journalctl on Linux, from the rotating router.log file on Windows.
